      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "IT'S A GLAM (1) boasts a strong record this course with nine wins and six minors from 25 tries. Placed last time (22.91) at this track in a Grade 4/5, finishing second and beaten 4.5 lengths. Looks the one to beat with even luck. ZIPPING GRESSIER (6) was quickly into stride and burnt early from out wide where he gave a sight, finishing second (23.08) and beaten 5 lengths over 400m at this track. Expecting another good run. MISS ELPHABA (7) is rarely far away but tends to find one better, placing 10 from 20 starts. Finished second (23.13) at this track latest and might be close to finding winning form again. Safe beginner but wide box to overcome and will need some luck. Expecting another good run. MAKE YOUR STAND (2) has been freshened for this and can hit the frame.",
